REMARKS
— The ocular peduncles in the specimens from the Norfolk Ridge (MNHN-IU-2014-16394) are much more slender than in the other specimens, and the carapace is finely granulose in the female (
9.9 mm
) and the smaller male (
7.1 mm
), faintly so in the larger male (
8.6 mm
).
